Pythons

Source: R/Pythons.R
Pythons.Rd

Downloaded (2023.02.16) Pythons trade data from the CITES Trade database.

Pythons

Format

A data frame with 1697301 rows and 20 variables:

Id

double Globally Unique Identifer for each import record

Year

integer Year of import

Appendix

character Relevant Appendix

Taxon

character Taxon

Class

character Class

Order

character Order

Family

character Family

Genus

character Genus

Term

character Term describing the trade (e.g. live, specimen, skins, bone, shoes, etc )

Quantity

double Number of objects (not always individuals)

Unit

character Unit describing Quantity

Importer

character Two letter country code for importing country

Exporter

character Two letter country code for exporting country

Origin

character Two letter country code for country of origin

Purpose

character 12 single letter codes Purpose_codes describing the trade purpose (e.g. commerical, scientific, etc.)

Source

character 11 single letter codes Source_codes describing the source of the trade (e.g. captive breeding, wild caught, etc.)

Reporter.type

character I= Importer, E= Exporter

Import.permit.RandomID

character Globally Unique Identifier

Export.permit.RandomID

character Globally Unique Identifier

Origin.permit.RandomID

character Globally Unique Identifier

Details

Dataset for testing functions in the package
